1 0 0 1 50 594 Tm (1. Executive Summary) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 580 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 566 Tm (This project implements BSD-style file locking in the mCertiKOS operating system. The) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 552 Tm (main purpose is to provide safe synchronization when multiple processes access the same) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 538 Tm (file concurrently. The implementation introduces shared and exclusive lock semantics,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 524 Tm (supports blocking and non-blocking behavior, and integrates lock management from) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 510 Tm (user-space API down to kernel-level inode state.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 496 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 482 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 468 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 454 Tm (2. Project Objectives) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 440 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 426 Tm (The key objectives of the project were:) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 412 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 398 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 384 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 370 Tm (1. Implement file locking semantics compatible with flock behavior.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 356 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 342 Tm (2. Support read-sharing through shared locks.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 328 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 314 Tm (3. Ensure exclusive write access through exclusive locks.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 300 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 286 Tm (4. Provide non-blocking lock acquisition mode.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 272 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 258 Tm (5. Integrate locking into the kernel file-system path.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 244 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 230 Tm (6. Validate functionality with comprehensive user-space tests.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 216 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 202 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 188 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 174 Tm (3. Locking Model and Semantics) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 160 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 146 Tm (The project supports the following operations:) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 132 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 118 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 104 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 90 Tm (- LOCK_SH: Acquire a shared lock.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 76 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 62 Tm (- LOCK_EX: Acquire an exclusive lock.) Tj
